Note:
Foundational error / option / either / try types for the Runa numeric
primitive layer.

This module exposes four parametric value types implemented uniformly
as Integer-tagged-pointer ADTs.  Each value is a 24-byte heap header
encoded as:

    offset 0:  tag        (Integer; type-specific discriminant)
    offset 8:  payload_a  (Integer or pointer; meaning depends on tag)
    offset 16: payload_b  (Integer or pointer; meaning depends on tag)

The bootstrap stage1 parser does not provide first-class generic-type
parameter syntax (no `Result<T, E>` form is recognized), so we represent
parametricity by storing arbitrary Integer-sized payloads.  Higher
layers must agree on the payload encoding for their T / E / L / R
types; primitives such as BigInts are already passed as opaque Integer
pointers, so the convention threads through directly.

CONSTRUCTION

For each type, the constructor procs (e.g. ok, err, some, none, left,
right, try_ok, try_err) allocate the 24-byte header and write the
discriminant and payloads.  Every constructor returns the header
pointer; the caller owns the header and the payloads it embeds.

OWNERSHIP

The Result / Option / Either / Try wrappers DO NOT take ownership of
their payload pointers.  Releasing the wrapper via result_free /
option_free / either_free / try_free deallocates the 24-byte header
ONLY.  Payloads must be freed separately by their original owner if
they require it; this is consistent with the BigInt and UInt64 buffer
conventions used throughout the numeric primitive layer.

PARAMETRIC POLYMORPHISM PATTERN

Because Runa stage1 has no generic-parameter syntax, the parametric T
in Result<T, E> is represented as an Integer-shaped slot.  When T is a
primitive Integer (e.g. a 64-bit count), the slot holds the value
directly.  When T is a heap object (e.g. a BigInt header pointer),
the slot holds the pointer.  Callers wishing to dispatch on T must do
so externally (the Result type itself is type-erased).

This convention is identical to the one used by string_core,
io_core, and the BigInt limb-buffer layer: an Integer slot is the
universal payload carrier in stage1.  Once stage1 receives generic-
parameter syntax this module's @Reasoning blocks will be updated to
make T / E / L / R the parser-recognised parameters; the runtime
representation will not change.

HIGHER-ORDER OPERATION DISPATCH

The functor / monadic helpers (map, map_err, and_then, or_else, fold,
recover) take an Integer-shaped function-pointer argument and invoke
it through call_indirect_1 from compiler/frontend/primitives/assembly/
call_indirect.runa.  That primitive loads the function pointer into rax,
marshals the single argument into rdi per the System V x86_64 calling
convention, and issues `call rax` -- a real indirect branch that runs
the supplied function and returns its result.  The function pointer is
obtained at the call site with the `$function_name` operator, which the
compiler lowers to `leaq <label>(%rip)` (the function's address).

This is the same proven indirect-call path used by the async, task, and
config subsystems.  map / and_then / or_else / fold / recover therefore
dispatch their mappers for real: a mapper that does work is executed and
its value flows back through the combinator.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/assembly/call_indirect.runa" as CallIndirect

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Layout offsets and tag values
Note: ============================================================================

Constant ADT_HEADER_SIZE as Integer is 24
Constant ADT_TAG_OFF as Integer is 0
Constant ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF as Integer is 8
Constant ADT_PAYLOAD_B_OFF as Integer is 16

Note: Result discriminants
Constant RESULT_TAG_OK as Integer is 1
Constant RESULT_TAG_ERR as Integer is 2

Note: Option / Maybe discriminants
Constant OPTION_TAG_SOME as Integer is 1
Constant OPTION_TAG_NONE as Integer is 2

Note: Either discriminants
Constant EITHER_TAG_LEFT as Integer is 1
Constant EITHER_TAG_RIGHT as Integer is 2

Note: Try discriminants.  Carries an optional cause pointer in payload_b
Note: when tag == TRY_TAG_ERR so that exception chaining is supported.
Constant TRY_TAG_OK as Integer is 1
Constant TRY_TAG_ERR as Integer is 2

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Allocator helpers
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "adt_alloc" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocates a 24-byte ADT header used by all four parametric types in
    this module.  Returned in a zero-initialized state.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single Layout.allocate followed by explicit zero of all three slots.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) constant-size allocation.  Frequently called on hot paths.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0 (NULL); callers MUST check.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let buf be Layout.allocate(ADT_HEADER_SIZE)
    If buf is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(buf, ADT_TAG_OFF, 0)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(buf, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF, 0)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(buf, ADT_PAYLOAD_B_OFF, 0)
    Return buf
End Process

Process called "adt_free" takes header as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Releases an ADT header.  Does NOT release the payload pointer(s);
    payload ownership is the caller's responsibility per the module
    contract.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Layout.deallocate guarded by a NULL check.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Double-free triggers the allocator canary.
    @End Security_Scope

    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Layout.deallocate(header)
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "adt_get_tag" takes header as Integer returns Integer:
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_int64(header, ADT_TAG_OFF)
End Process

Process called "adt_get_payload_a" takes header as Integer returns Integer:
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
End Process

Process called "adt_get_payload_b" takes header as Integer returns Integer:
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return Memory.memory_get_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_B_OFF)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Result<T, E>
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "ok" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs a Result in the success state carrying `value`.  The
    value's underlying type is opaque from the Result's perspective; it
    is treated as an Integer-sized payload (which for stage1 covers
    both raw 64-bit Integer values and 64-bit pointers to richer
    objects).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate a fresh ADT header, set the discriminant to RESULT_TAG_OK,
    and store the payload at slot A.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0 (NULL); callers MUST check.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let header be adt_alloc()
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_TAG_OFF, RESULT_TAG_OK)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF, value)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "err" takes error as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs a Result in the error state carrying `error`.  Like
    ok(), the error's underlying type is opaque to the Result.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate header, set discriminant to RESULT_TAG_ERR, store the
    error payload in slot A.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let header be adt_alloc()
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_TAG_OFF, RESULT_TAG_ERR)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF, error)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "is_ok" takes result as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Predicate: 1 if the Result is in the success state, 0 otherwise.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Inspect the discriminant.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL result is treated as not-ok (returns 0).
    @End Security_Scope

    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to RESULT_TAG_OK:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "is_err" takes result as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Predicate: 1 if the Result is in the error state, 0 otherwise.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Inspect the discriminant.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL result is treated as not-err (returns 0).
    @End Security_Scope

    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to RESULT_TAG_ERR:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "result_unwrap" takes result as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Extracts the success payload.  If the Result is in the error state
    the caller has violated the contract; we return 0 to remain total,
    but production code must guard with is_ok first.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Read slot A when tag is OK.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL result returns 0.  Error-state result returns 0; not a panic.
    @End Security_Scope

    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to RESULT_TAG_OK:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "result_unwrap_or" takes result as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Extracts the success payload when present, otherwise returns the
    caller-supplied default.  This is the safe, no-panic alternative
    to unwrap.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Inspect tag; return slot A on OK, else the default.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If result is equal to 0:
        Return default_value
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to RESULT_TAG_OK:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    End If
    Return default_value
End Process

Process called "result_unwrap_err" takes result as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Symmetric counterpart to unwrap: extracts the error payload.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Read slot A when tag is ERR.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL result returns 0; OK-state result returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to RESULT_TAG_ERR:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "result_map" takes result as Integer, mapper as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Functor map: if the Result is OK, apply `mapper` to the success
    payload and wrap the result in a fresh OK Result.  Error Results
    pass through unchanged (with a fresh allocation to preserve
    ownership symmetry).

    The `mapper` parameter is an Integer-typed function pointer.  The
    bootstrap-stage1 dispatch is via the indirect-call primitive
    __builtin_call_indirect_1 with one Integer-sized argument and one Integer-
    sized return.  Higher layers wrap this in a typed closure once
    closure syntax becomes available.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Dispatch on the discriminant; OK -> call mapper, rebuild OK.
    ERR -> copy the existing error payload into a fresh ERR.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus the mapper's own cost.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Mapper pointer must be valid; we do not validate it.
    @End Security_Scope

    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to RESULT_TAG_OK:
        Let value be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
        Let new_value be proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with mapper, value
        Return ok(new_value)
    End If
    Let error be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    Return err(error)
End Process

Process called "result_map_err" takes result as Integer, mapper as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Functor map over the error channel: if the Result is ERR, apply
    `mapper` to the error payload and wrap in a fresh ERR.  OK passes
    through unchanged.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Dispatch on the discriminant.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus the mapper's own cost.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Mapper pointer must be valid.
    @End Security_Scope

    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to RESULT_TAG_ERR:
        Let error_value be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
        Let new_error be proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with mapper, error_value
        Return err(new_error)
    End If
    Let value be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    Return ok(value)
End Process

Process called "result_and_then" takes result as Integer, mapper as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Monadic bind ("flat-map"): if the Result is OK, call `mapper` on
    the success payload to produce a NEW Result and return it directly.
    Error Results propagate unchanged.

    `mapper` is a function-pointer that takes an Integer and returns
    an Integer (which the caller must interpret as a new Result
    header).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Dispatch on discriminant; on OK, the mapper's return value IS the
    new Result.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus mapper cost.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Mapper pointer must be valid; mapper must return a valid Result.
    @End Security_Scope

    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to RESULT_TAG_OK:
        Let value be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
        Return proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with mapper, value
    End If
    Let error be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    Return err(error)
End Process

Process called "result_or_else" takes result as Integer, recovery as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Error-channel monadic bind: if the Result is ERR, call `recovery`
    with the error payload to produce a NEW Result.  OK passes through.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Dispatch on discriminant; on ERR, the recovery's return IS the new
    Result.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus recovery cost.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Recovery pointer must be valid; recovery must return a valid Result.
    @End Security_Scope

    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to RESULT_TAG_ERR:
        Let error_value be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
        Return proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with recovery, error_value
    End If
    Let value be Memory.memory_get_int64(result, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    Return ok(value)
End Process

Process called "result_free" takes result as Integer returns Integer:
    Return adt_free(result)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Option<T> / Maybe<T>
Note: Maybe is exposed as an alias for Option below.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "some" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs an Option holding `value`.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate header, set tag = SOME, payload A = value.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let header be adt_alloc()
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_TAG_OFF, OPTION_TAG_SOME)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF, value)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "none" returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs an empty Option.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate header, set tag = NONE; payload slots remain zero.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0 (a NULL OptIon is treated as NONE by
    is_none, so this is observationally compatible with the desired
    semantics on OOM).
    @End Security_Scope

    Let header be adt_alloc()
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_TAG_OFF, OPTION_TAG_NONE)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "is_some" takes option as Integer returns Integer:
    If option is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to OPTION_TAG_SOME:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "is_none" takes option as Integer returns Integer:
    If option is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to OPTION_TAG_NONE:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "option_unwrap" takes option as Integer returns Integer:
    If option is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to OPTION_TAG_SOME:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "option_unwrap_or" takes option as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    If option is equal to 0:
        Return default_value
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to OPTION_TAG_SOME:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    End If
    Return default_value
End Process

Process called "option_map" takes option as Integer, mapper as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Functor map: applies `mapper` to the inner value when present.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Tag dispatch; on SOME, call mapper and rewrap.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus mapper cost.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Mapper pointer must be valid.
    @End Security_Scope

    If option is equal to 0:
        Return none()
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to OPTION_TAG_SOME:
        Let value be Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
        Let new_value be proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with mapper, value
        Return some(new_value)
    End If
    Return none()
End Process

Process called "option_and_then" takes option as Integer, mapper as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Monadic bind: `mapper` returns a new Option that is propagated
    directly.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Tag dispatch.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus mapper cost.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Mapper pointer must be valid; mapper must return a valid Option.
    @End Security_Scope

    If option is equal to 0:
        Return none()
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to OPTION_TAG_SOME:
        Let value be Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
        Return proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with mapper, value
    End If
    Return none()
End Process

Process called "option_or_else" takes option as Integer, fallback as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Replaces a NONE Option with whatever the `fallback` function
    produces.  SOME passes through.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Tag dispatch; on NONE, call fallback with no useful argument (we
    pass 0).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus fallback cost.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Fallback pointer must be valid; must return a valid Option.
    @End Security_Scope

    If option is equal to 0:
        Return proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with fallback, 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to OPTION_TAG_NONE:
        Return proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with fallback, 0
    End If
    Let value be Memory.memory_get_int64(option, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    Return some(value)
End Process

Process called "option_free" takes option as Integer returns Integer:
    Return adt_free(option)
End Process

Note: Maybe<T> aliases mirror Option<T> verbatim.

Process called "maybe_some" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Return some(value)
End Process

Process called "maybe_none" returns Integer:
    Return none()
End Process

Process called "maybe_is_some" takes maybe as Integer returns Integer:
    Return is_some(maybe)
End Process

Process called "maybe_is_none" takes maybe as Integer returns Integer:
    Return is_none(maybe)
End Process

Process called "maybe_unwrap" takes maybe as Integer returns Integer:
    Return option_unwrap(maybe)
End Process

Process called "maybe_unwrap_or" takes maybe as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    Return option_unwrap_or(maybe, default_value)
End Process

Process called "maybe_map" takes maybe as Integer, mapper as Integer returns Integer:
    Return option_map(maybe, mapper)
End Process

Process called "maybe_and_then" takes maybe as Integer, mapper as Integer returns Integer:
    Return option_and_then(maybe, mapper)
End Process

Process called "maybe_or_else" takes maybe as Integer, fallback as Integer returns Integer:
    Return option_or_else(maybe, fallback)
End Process

Process called "maybe_free" takes maybe as Integer returns Integer:
    Return option_free(maybe)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Either<L, R>
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "left" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs an Either carrying a Left payload.  Left and Right are
    structurally symmetric; the convention in functional programming
    treats Left as the "error" or "fallback" side and Right as the
    "success" side, but this module places no semantics on the choice.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate header, set tag = LEFT, payload A = value.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let header be adt_alloc()
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_TAG_OFF, EITHER_TAG_LEFT)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF, value)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "right" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs an Either carrying a Right payload.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate header, set tag = RIGHT, payload A = value.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let header be adt_alloc()
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_TAG_OFF, EITHER_TAG_RIGHT)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF, value)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "is_left" takes either as Integer returns Integer:
    If either is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(either, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to EITHER_TAG_LEFT:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "is_right" takes either as Integer returns Integer:
    If either is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(either, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to EITHER_TAG_RIGHT:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "either_unwrap_left" takes either as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Extracts the Left payload.  Returns 0 if the Either is in the Right
    state or NULL.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Tag check then slot A read.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If either is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(either, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to EITHER_TAG_LEFT:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(either, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "either_unwrap_right" takes either as Integer returns Integer:
    If either is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(either, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to EITHER_TAG_RIGHT:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(either, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "either_swap" takes either as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Swaps the Left/Right discriminant of the Either, returning a fresh
    Either whose payload is preserved but whose side is flipped.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Inspect tag, allocate a new header with the opposite tag.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0; NULL input returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If either is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(either, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    Let value be Memory.memory_get_int64(either, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    If tag is equal to EITHER_TAG_LEFT:
        Return right(value)
    End If
    If tag is equal to EITHER_TAG_RIGHT:
        Return left(value)
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "either_fold" takes either as Integer, left_fn as Integer, right_fn as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Eliminates an Either by dispatching to one of two functions
    depending on which side it carries.  Each function takes the
    payload and returns an Integer-shaped result.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Tag dispatch.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus the chosen function's cost.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Both function pointers must be valid.
    @End Security_Scope

    If either is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(either, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    Let value be Memory.memory_get_int64(either, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    If tag is equal to EITHER_TAG_LEFT:
        Return proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with left_fn, value
    End If
    If tag is equal to EITHER_TAG_RIGHT:
        Return proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with right_fn, value
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "either_free" takes either as Integer returns Integer:
    Return adt_free(either)
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Try<T>
Note: Try wraps the Result interface with a "panic/exception" overlay
Note: that supports cause-chaining; payload_a holds the success value or
Note: error message pointer, and payload_b holds an optional cause Try
Note: header for the error path.
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "try_ok" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs a Try in the success state with `value`.  Payload B
    is left zero (no cause chain on the success path).
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate header, set tag = TRY_TAG_OK, payload A = value.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let header be adt_alloc()
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_TAG_OFF, TRY_TAG_OK)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF, value)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_B_OFF, 0)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "try_err" takes message as Integer, cause_optional as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Constructs a Try in the error state.  `message` is an Integer-shaped
    payload (typically a pointer to a null-terminated string allocated
    elsewhere).  `cause_optional` is either 0 (no inner cause) or a
    pointer to another Try header that triggered this failure, enabling
    exception-style cause chains across FFI / runtime boundaries.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate header, set tag, payload A = message, payload B = cause.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Allocation failure returns 0.  The cause pointer is NOT validated;
    callers must guarantee its lifetime exceeds this Try's lifetime.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let header be adt_alloc()
    If header is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_TAG_OFF, TRY_TAG_ERR)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF, message)
    Memory.memory_set_int64(header, ADT_PAYLOAD_B_OFF, cause_optional)
    Return header
End Process

Process called "try_is_ok" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to TRY_TAG_OK:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "try_is_err" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to TRY_TAG_ERR:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "try_get_value" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Extracts the success value when the Try is in the OK state.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Tag check, then slot A.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL or ERR-state Try returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to TRY_TAG_OK:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "try_get_message" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Extracts the error message (typically a string pointer) when the
    Try is in the ERR state.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Tag check, then slot A.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL or OK-state Try returns 0.
    @End Security_Scope

    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to TRY_TAG_ERR:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "try_get_cause" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Extracts the optional cause-chain pointer when the Try is in the
    ERR state.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Tag check, then slot B.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    NULL or OK-state Try returns 0.  Returning 0 in the absence of a
    cause is by design.
    @End Security_Scope

    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to TRY_TAG_ERR:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_PAYLOAD_B_OFF)
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "try_recover" takes t as Integer, recovery as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    If the Try is in the ERR state, invoke `recovery` with the error
    message to produce a new Try.  OK passes through unchanged.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Tag dispatch.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1) plus recovery cost.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Recovery pointer must be valid.
    @End Security_Scope

    If t is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to TRY_TAG_ERR:
        Let message be Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
        Return proc call_indirect_1 from CallIndirect with recovery, message
    End If
    Let value be Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    Return try_ok(value)
End Process

Process called "try_or_else" takes t as Integer, default_value as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Yields the success value when present, otherwise returns the
    caller-supplied default.  Mirrors result_unwrap_or.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Tag dispatch.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Total.
    @End Security_Scope

    If t is equal to 0:
        Return default_value
    End If
    Let tag be Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_TAG_OFF)
    If tag is equal to TRY_TAG_OK:
        Return Memory.memory_get_int64(t, ADT_PAYLOAD_A_OFF)
    End If
    Return default_value
End Process

Process called "try_free" takes t as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Releases a Try header.  Does NOT release the cause chain in
    payload_b automatically; callers that built a chain must free
    each Try individually to preserve composability.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Layout.deallocate on the header.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    O(1).
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Double-free triggers the allocator canary.
    @End Security_Scope

    Return adt_free(t)
End Process
